questions.question_text:
Consider a small dataset comprised of N = 7 observations
x = [3, 4, 6, 13, 16, 18, 20].
Suppose a k-means algorithm is applied to the dataset with K = 3 clusters and using Euclidean distances. At a given stage of the algorithm the data is partitioned into the blocks:
{3, 4}, {6, 13, 16}, {18, 20}
What clustering will the k-means algorithm eventually converge to?

A. {}, {3, 4, 6, 13, 16}, {18, 20}
B. {3, 4, 6}, {13}, {16, 18, 20}
C. {3, 4}, {6, 13, 16, 18}, {20}
D. {3, 4}, {6, 13}, {16, 18, 20}
